    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 557,
    "last_activity_date" : 1400493828,
    "last_edit_date" : 1400493828,
    "creation_date" : 1319844383,
    "answer_id" : 7935873,
    "question_id" : 7935858,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#split-java.lang.String-\"><code>java.lang.String.split</code></a> splits on regular expressions, and <code>.</code> in a regular expression means \"any character\".</p>\n\n<p>Try <code>temp.split(\"\\\\.\")</code>.</p>\n"
